properties.headline: Dense Fog Advisory issued January 13 at 2:33AM CST until January 13 at 8:00AM CST by NWS Wichita KS
properties.description:
* WHAT...Visibility of one quarter mile or less in dense fog.

* WHERE...Cowley, Chautauqua and Montgomery Counties.

* WHEN...Until 8 AM CST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Hazardous driving conditions due to low visibility.
Due to low temperatures, expect some slick conditions as the
fog is likely to freeze to road surfaces.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Dense freezing fog will continue to develop
overnight, especially where there is snow on the ground or
standing water. Use caution on roadways as they may become
slick. Slow down and increase following distance for safety.
properties.instruction:
If driving, slow down, use your headlights, and leave plenty of
distance ahead of you.

NWSheadline: DENSE FOG ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 8 AM CST THIS MORNING
